  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, **Facebook does not provide a feature that allows you to see who specifically views your profile.** This is a deliberate design choice to protect user privacy.\n\nHere's why and what you *can* see:\n\n*   **Privacy Concerns:** Facebook prioritizes user privacy. Allowing people to see who viewed their profile would likely deter users from browsing and using the platform freely. It could also lead to stalking or harassment.\n*   **Data Overload:** The amount of data generated by tracking every profile view would be immense and potentially overwhelming for Facebook's servers.\n\n**What you *CAN* see on Facebook:**\n\n*   **Post Engagement:** You can see who has liked, commented on, or shared your posts. This gives you an indication of who is seeing your content.\n*   **Story Views:** You can see who has viewed your Facebook Story.\n*   **Profile Visits (on Business/Creator Pages):** If you have a Facebook Page (for a business, public figure, etc.), you can see some aggregated data about profile visits within your page insights. This won't show *specific* individuals, but it will give you a count of the number of visits and some demographic information.\n*   **Friend Requests:** You can see who has sent you friend requests, which indicates they may have viewed your profile.\n*   **Mutual Friends:** If you have mutual friends with someone, they may have come across your profile through shared connections.\n*   **Messenger Contacts:** If someone messages you, it's highly likely they've viewed your profile.\n\n**Be Wary of Third-Party Apps and Extensions:**\n\n*   There are many third-party apps and browser extensions that claim to show you who viewed your Facebook profile. **These are generally scams or malware.** They often require access to your Facebook account and can steal your personal information or spread spam to your friends.\n*   **Do not trust these apps.** They violate Facebook's terms of service and can compromise your security and privacy.\n\n**In summary:**\n\nFacebook does not offer a feature to see who views your profile due to privacy reasons. Be cautious of any third-party apps that claim to provide this functionality, as they are likely scams. Focus on understanding engagement with your posts and stories as a better indicator of who is seeing your content.\n",
